x4freetext: A PULSE LENGTH OF 150NS AND A REPRATE OF 192HZ.
MOUNTED IN A BORON SLEEVE TO REDUCE BACKGROUND OF
IT DETECTED THE FISSION NEUTRONS FROM A METALLIC
URANIUM SAMPLE. THIS DETECTION SYSTEM WAS DESCRIBED
IN D.B.GAYTHER ET AL., PROC.PANEL NEUTR.STAND.
IT WAS DESIGNED BY M.C.MOXON WITH GLASS FROM
KOCH-LIGHT AND WAS WATCHED BY TWO RCA 8854 PM TUBES
OF LOW NOISE QUALITY, ITS EFFICIENCY VARYING NOT
THIS DETECTOR SERVED AS THE LITHIUM SAMPLE AT
THE INTERVAL 2 KEV TO 10 KEV, WHERE THE CROSS SECTION
THE SHAPE OF THE CROSS SECTIONS LI-6(N,A)/U-235(N,F)
IS MEASURED. THE EVALUATED CROSS SECTION OF U-235
IS THEN USED AS SHAPE OF THE U-235 CROSS SECTION
AND THE SHAPE OF THE LI-6 CROSS SECTION IS OBTAINED.
THIS SHAPE IS THAN NORMALIZED USING THE AVERAGE
VALUE OF THE LITHIUM CROSS SECTION BETWEEN 2
PROMPT NEUTRONS FROM U-235 FISSION IN THE
ALPHA PARTICLES FROM LI-6(N,A) IN THE LITHIUM
.MONITOR EFFICIENCIES WITH REGARD TO INCIDENT N-ENERGY
SPECTRUM AND ANGULAR DISTR. (0.9 PC FOR LI-GLASS
.ALSO FOR RESONANCE SCATTERING IN AL CONTAINER OF
.SAMPLE THICKNESS CORR. CARRIED OUT BY MONTE-CARLO.
